	(1882, 20055, 'EN', 1, 'This chart shows the level of reporting of non-fatal accidents. It is based on the number of fatal accidents. The reporting level is estimated as follows: In the EU there are in average 1,109 non-fatal accidents per one fatal accident (EU 15). The registered fatal accidents of each Member State are multiplied with this ratio, i.e. with 1,109. If the result of this calculation is in line with the registered number of accidents the reporting level is 100 %. Background is the assumption that the registration of fatal accidents is close to 100%, whilst there is often a large share of cases of non-fatal accidents that are not reported (so-called ‘Underreporting’) See also <a target="_blank" href=" http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Accidents_at_work_statistics">Eurostat</a>.');
